        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-12 08:15:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n\nWhy almost all comments have been ignored and noted with a \"todo later\"?\nThese things should be, in my opinion, done prior to merging such a big chunk of code, simply because I think that later on there will be things that are more important than fixing code quality in a component that works for now.\n\nAlso, from what I noticed in the comments, there will be many things fixed there that will impact how this component works. \nSo delivering this at top speed just for the sake of delivering it and then testing it prior to the fixes make little sense to me.\nIMHO tests and refactoring should never be done once implementation is in place, because then, tests start to reflect current implementation, not requirements.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
